FBIS4-61142 "drsov086_s_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-086 Daily Report 4 May 1994 Georgia Evacuated Greeks Returning to Abkhazia Evacuated Greeks Returning to Abkhazia AU0305172494 Tbilisi NOVAYA GAZETA in Russian No. 7 (73) Apr 94 p 3 AU0305172494 Tbilisi NOVAYA GAZETA Russian BFN ["BS-Press" report: "The Greeks Are Returning to Abkhazia"] [Text] Dionisios Kalamvrezos, the Greek consul in Moscow, stated that the majority of Greeks who were evacuated during military actions in Abkhazia and sent to their historic homeland were gradually returning to their places of permanent residence. The Greek authorities are not preventing the return to Abkhazia of refugees from among their compatriots. However, they are demanding appropriate guarantees for their security. According to figures given by the consulate, there were between 16,000 and 17,000 Greeks living in Abkhazia before the outbreak of the war. The total number remaining there today is 3,000.
